                        <join result="offenceVictim" targOrder="Y" targets="t18310630-312-off1631 t18310630-312-victim2195"></join>
                     </persName>
                  , which had lately before been stolen, he well knowing the same to have been stolen
            </rs>; against the Statute.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18310630-312-person2196">
                  BRYNE 
                  COX
               <interp inst="t18310630-312-person2196" type="surname" value="COX"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18310630-312-person2196" type="given" value="BRYNE"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18310630-312-person2196" type="gender" value="indeterminate"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am eleven years of age. On the 25th of May I lost a 6d.; I stood crying at my mother's door - the prisoner came up, and asked what was the matter; I said I had lost 6d., which my mother gave me to get some potatoes - he said, "Never mind - bring me 4lbs. of rags, and I will give you 2d. for them;" he came into my father's passage, and I gave him my own coat and two waistcoats - he said that was not enough; I then brought my father's two pairs of breeches and two pairs of trousers; he gave me 2d. for them - I then brought him down one pair of drawers, two frocks and a gown, and he gave me 2d. more; I then brought him two petticoats and another frock, and he gave me 1 1/2d. for them - he asked me if I should have any more to-morrow; I said No - I am sure the prisoner is the man.</p>
               <p>HUGH COX. The things were worth 1l. to me, at least - my wife went after the prisoner, and found him; I went to him, and asked if he was not ashamed to induce my boy to sell him all this property for 5 1/2d. - he said, "I am not ashamed - I sold one pair of the trousers to a man for 1s. 3d., and the rest were torn up in rags."</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18310630-312-person2197">
                  HERBERT 
                  PRIDDON
               <interp inst="t18310630-312-person2197" type="surname" value="PRIDDON"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18310630-312-person2197" type="given" value="HERBERT"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18310630-312-person2197" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            , I am a Police-constable. The<xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="183106300139"></xptr>prisoner said, in my hearing, that he sold one pair of breeches, for 1s. 3d.</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence. They were nothing but rags - there was only one pair of breeches.</p>
               <p>
